# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CRM Frontend - Environment Configuration Template
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# IMPORTANT: Copy this file to .env and fill in the actual values
# .env file is git-ignored and should NEVER be committed
#
# Location: crm-frontend/.env
#
# After editing:
# 1. Save the file
# 2. Restart the frontend development server
# 3. Verify in browser console for any config errors
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend API Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8081
# Backend HTTP endpoint
# Used for: All REST API calls
# Development: http://localhost:8081
# Production: https://your-backend-domain.com

VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8081/ws
# Backend WebSocket endpoint
# Used for: Real-time chat, notifications
# Development: ws://localhost:8081/ws
# Production: wss://your-backend-domain.com/ws (note: wss for HTTPS)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudinary Configuration (Image Upload)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
# Get from: https://cloudinary.com
# Steps:
#   1. Create free account
#   2. Go to Dashboard
#   3. Copy your Cloud Name
# Used for: Avatar uploads, image storage

VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=taskflow_avatars
# Get from: https://cloudinary.com/console/settings/upload
# Steps:
#   1. Go to Upload Settings
#   2. Create Unsigned Upload Preset named "taskflow_avatars"
#   3. Keep folder as "crm-avatars" or your choice
# Used for: Client-side image uploads without backend auth

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth2 Configuration - Google
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here
# Same as backend GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
# Format: XXXXXXXXXXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX.apps.googleusercontent.com
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com
# Used for: Google login button

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth2 Configuration - GitHub
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id_here
# Same as backend GITHUB_CLIENT_ID
# Get from: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Used for: GitHub login button

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env
#    Command: cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in the values:
#    - Point to your backend API URL
#    - Use Cloudinary credentials (optional, skip if not using image upload)
#    - Use same OAuth IDs as backend
#
# 3. DO NOT COMMIT .env
#    This file should stay local only
#    It will be automatically ignored by Git
#
# 4. Restart the frontend dev server
#    npm run dev
#    or in your IDE
#
# 5. Verify in browser
#    Open http://localhost:3000 or 5173
#    Open browser console (F12) for any errors
#    Check that API calls go to correct backend
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ENVIRONMENT URLS BY STAGE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# DEVELOPMENT (Local):
#   VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8081
#   VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8081/ws
#
# STAGING:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api-staging.example.com
#   VITE_WS_URL=wss://api-staging.example.com/ws
#
# PRODUCTION:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
#   VITE_WS_URL=wss://api.example.com/ws
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL SERVICES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Cloudinary (Image Upload):
#   Not required for development
#   If skipped: Avatar upload will fail gracefully
#   Optional for: User profile pictures, task attachments
#
# OAuth Credentials:
#   Not required for testing
#   If skipped: Login/Register buttons will show but not work
#   Optional for: Social login (Google, GitHub)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Problem: "Failed to connect to backend"
#   Solution: Check VITE_API_URL points to running backend
#   Command: curl http://localhost:8081/actuator/health
#
# Problem: "WebSocket connection failed"
#   Solution: Check VITE_WS_URL is correct
#   Verify: Backend is running on correct port
#
# Problem: "Image upload not working"
#   Solution: Provide Cloudinary credentials or skip this feature
#   Fallback: Backend file upload works without Cloudinary
#
# Problem: "OAuth login not working"
#   Solution: Verify OAuth IDs match backend
#   Check: OAuth credentials in Google/GitHub console
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

